u i ka nane.\n56:34 mk:m1 A no ka mea, kēia koʻu wā ʻehā paha kēia nei wau e hoʻolohe mai nei iā ʻou^^ iā ʻoukou.\n56:40 LK  ʻAe.\n56:41 mk:m1 A,\n56:43 LK  ʻAe.\n56:43 mk:m1 Me aʻu, mai koʻu wā liʻiliʻi mai ka ʻāina nui nō hoʻi wau o Hawaiʻi.\n56:48 LK  ʻO hea o Hawaiʻi?  ʻO Puna?\n56:50 mk:m1 A ʻo ia.\n56:51 LK  ʻO Puna, ʻāina kaulana kēlā i ka nane.\n56:54 mk:m1 ʻO ia hoʻi.  \n56:55 LK  ^^^\n56:56 mk:m1 I nā, ^^^\n56:57 LK  ʻĀina kaulana i ka nane ʻo Puna.\n56:59 mk:m1 ʻĒ.  Kelep^^ au a hoʻolohe au, hoʻolohe ʻoe iā. ʻou^^ iā ʻoukou i ka walaʻau ʻana, hoʻopuka ana ka poʻe iā ʻoe i kēlā hana ʻana i ka mea lau hala nō hoʻi.\n57:08 LK  ʻAe.\n57:09 mk:m1 A hoʻolohe ana wau kekahi, kekahi poʻe nonoi mai ana iā ʻoe.  ʻOiaʻiʻo nō akā kekahi poʻe ʻaʻole paha i maopopo pono ka mea ʻana, ka hana ʻana nō hoʻi o ka lau hala.\n57:20 LK  ʻAe, ʻae.\n57:21 mk:m1 ʻO ia hoʻi me ka, me ka, mea o ka pāpale a, ka loulu.\n57:26 LK  ʻAe.  ʻO ka loulu.\n57:27 mk:m1 A ʻo ia nō hoʻi, no ka mea,\n57:29 LK  Pāpale keʻokeʻo kēlā.\n57:30 mk:m1 ʻO ia hoʻi.\n57:31 LK  Lau keʻo^^\n57:32 mk:m1 ʻO koʻu wā liʻiliʻi, o, paʻa^^ paʻanaʻau hoʻi au.  ʻO ia ke kumu hoʻolohe wau.\n57:36 LK  ʻĒ.  A pehea ʻoukou i hoʻomākaukau i^^ a, hoʻomākaukau ai ka,\n57:39 mk:m1 He mea nui ka hana.  Nui ka hana !!\n57:40 LK  He ʻae, he hana nui.  Hoʻomaʻū paha ʻoukou i ka lau, i loko o ka, i loko o ke kai?\n57:47 mk:m1 ʻAʻole.  ʻOkoʻa mākou.\n57:49 LK  ʻOkoʻa.  ʻAʻole ʻoukou hoʻomaʻū i ka lau.  Lau ʻōpiopio kēia?\n57:54 mk:m1 Kuke aku ʻoe, pau a hoʻokaulaʻi ʻoe.\n57:55 LK  ʻŌ, kupa.\n57:56 mk:m1 A ʻo ia.\n57:57 LK  ʻĒ.\n57:58 mk:m1 Pau, a kaulaʻi aku nō hoʻi i kēia mea i ka lā.  Na ka lā nō hoʻi i mea mai. Hoʻokeʻokeʻo mai a keʻokeʻo hoʻi kēlā mea.\n58:05 LK  ʻAʻole hoʻokomo i loko o ka ʻeke huluhulu e kaulaʻi ai.\n58:09 mk:m1 ʻAʻole.\n58:10 LK  ʻAʻole.\n58:10 mk:m1 ʻAʻole.\n58:11 LK  ʻAe.  ʻAʻohe like mea melemele ka lau?\n58:14 mk:m1 Akā, you know, melemele nō ke mea ʻoe i waho loa, i ka lōʻihi ʻana o wa^^ o waho.\n58:20 LK  ʻĒ, ʻē.\n58:22 mk:m1 A ʻo ia ke kumu i noʻonoʻo aku nei wau i kēia pō, hoʻolohe mai ana iā ʻoukou kēia pō.  A makemake wau^^ ʻAʻole wau i lohe i ka nane.  ʻO ia ke kumu, makemake wau nonoi iā ʻoukou e hoʻopaʻanaʻau ʻoukou i ka nane.\n58:31 LK  ʻĒ, ʻē.  He na^^ he nane kaʻu iā ʻoe.\n58:36 mk:m1 A ʻo ia.\n58:37 LK  ʻAe.  Eia. ^^^ ʻEkolu pā ka loaʻa ʻana i ka wai.\n58:43 mk:m1 He aha ka hāʻina !!\n58:44 LK  He n^^ ʻeā?\n58:46 mk:m1 Pane hou mai ana ʻoe.\n58 47   {Uhu.}\n58:49 LK  ʻAe.  ʻEkolu pā ka loaʻa ʻana i ka wai.\n58:55 mk:m1 ʻEkolu pā.\n58:56 LK  Kuailo?\n58:58 mk:m1 ʻAʻole, ʻaʻole loaʻa iaʻu.\n58:59 LK  ʻAe. ^^^  ʻO ka niu.  He pūnāwai kēia kau i ka lewa.  ʻEkolu pā ka loaʻa ʻana i ka wai.\n58908 mk:m1 ʻAe.  ʻOkoʻa nō kekahi poʻe i ka mea ʻana. !! \n59:10 LK  ʻEā?\n59:11 mk:m1 kēnā, kēnā nane.\n59:12 LK  ʻO ka ʻili o ka, o ka niu, ʻo ka pulu a ʻo ka iwi o ka niu.  A loaʻa i ka wai.\n59:17 mk:m1 ʻO ia nō, ʻo ia nō.\n59:18 LK  ʻAe.  ʻEkolu pā. ^^^\n59:20 mk:m1 A ʻo ia.\n59:21 LK  A he aha kāu nane?\n59:24 mk:m1 ^^^\n59:25 LK  ^^^\n59:25 mk:m1 He nane nō kaʻu.  Akā nō naʻe i ka poʻe Hawaiʻi, ua, ua maʻa lākou.  A, ka noʻonoʻo ʻana paha ua mea, akā nō naʻe ka hāʻina, mea maikaʻi hoʻi ia.\n59:38 LK  ʻAe.  A he aha kāu nane?\n59:43 mk:m1 ʻO wai, ʻo wau?\n59:43 LK  ʻEā?  Pehea?\n59:48 mk:m1 Kuʻu wahi kanaka, ʻaʻole {mū,} a ua poina wau.\n59:52 LK  Poina?\n59:52 mk:m1 {Mū.}\n59:53 LK  ^^^\n59:54 mk:m1 No ka mea, i loko wau o ka hui koa ma mua o ka hele ʻana mai i waho nei.  ʻUmi makahiki me ka hapa.\n59:59 LK  ʻĒ, ʻē.\n60:00 mk:m1 I ka hemo ʻana mai mai ka hui koa, lōlō.  ʻAʻohe poʻe walaʻau Hawaiʻi iā ʻoe i loko ola.  A pau ka mea, make ana.\n60:09 LK  ʻAe.  Mahalo nui kou kele^^ ʻana, kelepona ʻana mai nei.\n60:12 mk:m1 Mahalo iā ʻoe i ka hoʻowehewehe ʻana mai nei iaʻu.\n60:14 LK  He aha?  ʻAe.\n60:15 mk:m1 Mahalo nui loa iā ʻoe i kou hoʻowehewehe ʻana mai nei iaʻu.  A hui hou nō kākou.  E hoʻolohe aku wau nō hoʻi iā ʻoukou.\n60:22 LK  ʻAe.  I kēia Kepakemapa, no ka mea, e hoʻomaha ana kākou, mea, mākou i kēia kauwela.\n60:27 mk:m1 I ka wā hea?\n60:28 LK  E hoʻomaha ana nā^^ Hoʻomaha ana ke kula no kēia kauwela.\n60:34 mk:m1 ʻO kēia?\n60:35 LK  ʻĒ.  No laila, ʻaʻole^^ ʻO kēia ka hope loa o ka, kā mākou papahana.\n60:40 mk:m1 ʻO kēia manawa e pau ʻoukou?\n60:42 LK  A, ʻae.\n60:43 mk:m1 Hoʻomaha ana.\n60:43 LK  E hoʻomaha ana.  A hoʻomaka hou ana paha i loko o Kepakemapa.\n60:47 mk:m1 ʻŌ, ʻo ia kā.\n60:48 LK  ʻAe.\n60:49 mk:m1 Mahalo nui loa iā ʻoe.\n60:50 LK  Mahalo nui iā ʻoe i kou lohe ʻana mai.\n60:52 mk:m1 Aloha nō.\n60:53 LK  ʻAe, aloha.\n60:56 DK  Pau koke ka manawa.\n60:57 LK  ʻAe.\n60:58 DK  Nui ka poʻe ma ke kelepona. !!\n60:59 LK  No laila, ua hiki mai kākou i ka hopena o kā mākou papahana.  Ma mua nō naʻe o ka hoʻopau ʻana o kēia papahana, makemake au e hoʻomanaʻo hou iā ʻoukou e nā mea e makemake ana e hele mai i kēia ʻaha ʻōlelo Hawaiʻi, ka mua kēia o ka ʻaha ʻōlelo Hawaiʻi e mālama ʻia nei ma ke kula, ma, ma ke Kula ʻo Kamehameha.  Inā makemake ʻoukou e hele mai i kēia ʻaha ʻōlelo Hawaiʻi, e kelepona mua iā Mrs. Bernie ma ke Kula ʻo Kamehameha.  A eia ka helu, helu ʻei^^ ʻewalu ʻehā ʻelima, ʻeono ʻeono ʻekolu ʻekahi.  A ʻo nā haumāna i kōkua lokomaikaʻi mai i kēia ahiahi ma kēia papahana, ʻo Tai Crouch ka mea i ʻōlelo ai ma ʻōlelo haole, me Pakele Freitas lāua ʻo Kiana Nāone ma ke kamaʻilio ʻana no Oʻahu, me Kuʻulei Kaikainahaole no ka haʻiʻōlelo ʻana ʻo ka manu kōlea.  A ʻo Kaniela Akaka, ʻo Pila Wilson me Eldon Akamine nā mea i, i hīmeni ai a i hoʻokani ai i ka pila.  A mahalo nui iā ʻoe, e Kahananui wahine i kou kipa ʻana mai i kēia ahiahi.  A me nā makamaka lehulehu i kōkua lokomaikaʻi mai i kēia papahana ʻo Ka Leo Hawaiʻi.  A mahalo nui iā ʻoukou e nā mea e hoʻolohe ana.  A aloha nui iā ʻoukou a pau loa.  A hui hou aku kākou.\n62:40 Hawaiʻi Aloha\n62:47 KS ## ʻAnoʻai ke aloha e nā pua o ka ʻāina.  Ua pā iho nei ko ʻoukou mau pepeiao i Ka Leo Hawaiʻi o ke ahiahi a me nā mele aloha o ka ʻāina, me he kahawai lā, e ʻōlino mau, e nanahe mau, a e nani mau.  Aloha a nui loa iā ʻoukou a pau, a hui hou aku kākou.\n  > E Hawaiʻi e kuʻu one hānau ē, hānau ē\n  Kuʻu home kulaiwi nei\n  ʻOli nō au i nā pono lani ou, lani ou\n  E Hawaiʻi aloha ē\n\n  E hauʻoli e nā ʻōpio Hawaiʻi nei\n  ʻOli ē, ʻoli ē, ʻoli ē, ʻoliʻoli ē\n  Mai nā aheahe makani e pā mai nei, pā mai nei\n64:21  Mau ke aloha no Hawaiʻi',FALSE,'2023-08-19 01:54:38','2023-08-19 02:01:57.310252');
